article.headline: Coll. of Charleston 68, Elon 60
article.story: ASHEVILLE, N.C. -- Andrew Lawrence scored 19 points and Willis Hall added a double-double as the third-seeded College of Charleston defeated No. 2 seed Elon 68-60 in the Southern Conference semifinals Sunday night. Hall had 16 points and 10 rebounds for the Cougars (24-9), who will face top-seeded Davidson in the championship game Monday at 7 p.m. Lucas Troutman paced the Phoenix (21-11) with 23 points, while Josh Bonney added 15 off the bench. Charleston opened with an 11-0 run and added an 8-0 stretch later in the half to lead 25-19 at the intermission. Elon's Kevin Blake hit a foul shot to pull the Phoenix within 60-56 with 28 seconds remaining, but the Cougars hit 8 of 8 foul shots after to stymie the comeback. The win is the Cougars' fourth straight. Charleston has only won the conference title once, in 1999 with a 77-57 win over Appalachian State.
